4. Field Geometry Operators

These are operations on the 4 fields. These operators describe how fields behave on the graph

4.1 Field Density

ρ_α(R,t) = (1/|R|) Σ_{x∈R} Φ_α(x,t)

Explanation

Measures average field value in region R

Region R is defined by blanket (boundary)

Intuition

High density → field concentrated

Low density → field sparse



Meaning:
 Average field strength in region R

4.2 Field Gradient

∇_G Φ_α(i,t) = Σ_{j∈N_c(i)} [Φ_α(j,t) − Φ_α(i,t)] / d_G(i,j)

 N_c(i) → certified neighbors 

 d_G → shortest path distance 

Meaning:
 Change of field across graph


Explanation

Measures change across neighbors

Uses only certified edges (E_c)

Intuition

High gradient → strong change / instability

Low gradient → uniform region

4.3 Field Curvature

κ_α(i,t) = ∇_G² Φ_α(i,t)
         = Σ_{j∈N_c(i)} [∇_G Φ_α(j,t) − ∇_G Φ_α(i,t)] / d_G(i,j)

Meaning:
 Second-order variation (instability / stress)



Explanation

Measures change of the gradient

Detects:

stress zones

rapid transitions

Intuition

High curvature → unstable region

Negative curvature → stable attractor

4.4 Field Flux

J_α(∂R,t) = Σ_{e crossing ∂R, e∈E_c} Φ_α(e,t)

Meaning:
 Field flow across boundary



Explanation

Measures flow across region boundary

Only valid through certified edges

Intuition

High flux → strong interaction across boundary

Low flux → isolated region

4.5 Semantic Curvature (Global)

χ(G) = Tr(M L_G⁺ Mᵀ)

 L_G → graph Laplacian 

 L_G⁺ → pseudoinverse 

 M → semantic adjacency 

Meaning:
 Mismatch between structure and meaning



Explanation

Measures mismatch between:

graph structure

semantic meaning

Intuition

High χ → structure contradicts meaning

χ → 0 → perfect alignment

